@Node Salvation " Salvation !"


      If you define a variable preceding its name by a '_' character, it will be valid !


      @{B}Example:@{UB}

            def and                 -> This is incorrect !

            def _and                -> This is valid 8-)


@Endnode
@Node info2 " More info "

      On this current version (v1.01), ECT recognizes all the stuff known by Amiga_E, that includes now the OS lib calls like 'DisplayBeep' or 'ChangeMode', etc ... Well, at least it should; If you find some function that isn't recognized, you must type EXACTLY it (that is, using upper and lower case as you'll have to do using Amiga_E before ECaseTool).

      Please note that *all* MODULE calls, such as 'AddConfigDev' on expansion.m or others, still aren't supported - they're a lot, so it would be very demanding (slow!) for ECT !

      Speaking on slowness, I was surprised to see that I didn't found any noticeable slowdown with this full version, comparing with the previous (which hadn't without support for the OS lib calls) ... At least on a 68030 running at 50Mhz. OK, that makes a me a nice programmer ?!


       Click @{" here " link Words} if you want to know what commands ECT can handle ...


@Endnode

